Theorem 1: The "Buy Everything, Refund the Worst" Principle
When to use it: You need to maximize the count of items (or minimize the sum of items for a fixed count) subject to a strict budget constraint.

The Law: Instead of trying to cleverly pick the best items one by one, be entirely greedy. 
Throw every item into a cart (a Max-Heap Priority Queue). If your total cost exceeds the budget, instantly pop() the single most expensive item in the cart and throw it away.

The Strategy: The heap guarantees that whatever remains inside it is the absolute cheapest possible combination of elements you've seen so far.
